==Abstract==

This IIP describes bloom filters for SPV clients to receive only relevant transactions. It is adapted from BIP 37 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Full blocks contain many transactions irrelevant to a particular wallet. Bloom filters allow lightweight clients to receive only transactions matching their addresses, reducing bandwidth significantly.

==Specification==

===Messages===

'''filterload''': Set the bloom filter
<pre>
filter:     []byte   // Filter data
nHashFuncs: uint32   // Number of hash functions
nTweak:     uint32   // Random tweak
nFlags:     uint8    // Update flags
</pre>

'''filteradd''': Add data to the filter
<pre>
data: []byte   // Element to add
</pre>

'''filterclear''': Remove the filter
<pre>
(empty)
</pre>

===Bloom Filter Parameters===

* Maximum filter size: 36,000 bytes
* Maximum hash functions: 50
* Hash function: MurmurHash3

===Matching===

A transaction matches the filter if any of:
* A txid matches
* An outpoint (txid:vout) matches
* Any data element in scriptSig matches
* Any data element in scriptPubKey matches

===Privacy Note===

Bloom filters leak information about wallet addresses. For better privacy, use compact block filters (IIP-16, IIP-17).

